
[1]suffering

   SUF'FERING, ppr. Bearing; undergoing pain, inconvenience or damage;
   permitting; allowing.

   SUF'FERING, n. The bearing of pain, inconvenience or loss; pain
   endured; distress, loss or injury incurred; as sufferings by pain or
   sorrow; sufferings by want or by wrongs.
